	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=143535><span id= >Seraphnie</span></a><br><span id=notbold>11 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well I suppose you probably already got yourself a gnome and began you break out of Feydweir. I wanted to post a few things in favor of the necro human. Always this choice is constantly being put down and I have to tell you that it's not bad at all!<br><br>With being a human you get two major benifits.<br><br>The first one is that you are loved. You are accepted in many city's with a few exceptions. You don't have to worry about catching the boat and you can always find water and lots of other stuff. (Food won't be a problem cause your gonna buy a spit/oven right...)<br><br><br>Another major plus is that human's have an extra exp bonus. I looked up the experience gain for humans, right here on Allakhazam actually.<br><br>No race gets exp. faster than human.&lt;---Thats a period.<br><br>Thats an ability that cannot be altered in any way with any item. I have never seen it mentioned anywhere that this is a major benefit for this race/class combo, but I'm sure that it is something that should seriously be taken into account. <br><br>The major complaint about the human is the Intelligents lag. Easy. Get mana items. 1 mana = 5 Int. Solves that problem. Whats 10 Int. when you have a 50+ mana robe? <br><br>As for the humans crappy sight, that in itself is solved by being a necro. You get all sorts of spells that enhance you sight. When I put my lvl 24 &quot;Shadow Sight&quot; spell on it makes the darkest dungeon almost a bright blue and when you get boneform it gives automatic ultravision. Many necro items will have this handy spell or light built in also. Just make sure you have the shadow site spell in an easy spot for when you return to gate point when you die. If that all that STILL does'nt work just turn up the brightness on your monitor a little.<br><br>I am a Female human necro myself, I never see anyone like me :) and Groups find me extremely useful. In fact, most times, i'm afraid to leave the keyboard in hopes they don't die. But that's just because I'm a necromancer I'm sure....<br><br>My second choice in best necro is Iksar. Because of the regen capabilites. I've heard it said that once you go lizard, you never go back....<br><br>Well that answers your question number 1...hehe I dare not go on...<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Feb 21 15:17:08 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Alienz & Seraphnie Sincraft<br>Mage and Necromancer dangerous duo</td></td></tr>
