	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=49677><span id=Guru>alaaraaf the Puissant</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>179 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p><span style='color: green;'><br>Hey<br><br>You start off indifferent in Thurgadin, before you do anything to change your faction with the dwarves.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is particularly handy for Iksar, since it's a whole city you can shop and bank in.<br><br>I would imagine that you need to have better than indifferent faction to do the Thurgadin armour quests.  However, building faction with the dwarves is <b>really</b> easy, by killing giants.  And of course, you'll be killing giants to get quest components.  So, that part shouldn't be an issue.<br><br>If you want to ally yourself with the giants, you'll have to do more work.  Particularly, if you had previously allied yourself with the dwarves.  (Dwarves and Giants are enemies.  So, you can't be friends with both.)  However, you have to kill dragons, for the Kael armour quests.  Which means that you'll need to be a higher level.<br><br>Quite a lot of people seem to start allied with dwarves and switch to giants, when they can kill dragons.  <br><br>Hope this helps.<br><br>AlAaraaf.<br></span style='color: green;'></p>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></td></tr>
